@LBA2_PRODUCT_NAME@ @LBA2_VERSION_STRING@
====================================================

@LBA2_PRODUCT_DESCRIPTION@

This is a portable build. No installer, no registry entries. Drop
@LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe wherever you want and run.


GAME DATA
---------

This fork doesn't include game data — you need a legitimate copy of
Little Big Adventure 2 / Twinsen's Odyssey from GOG, Steam, or your
original retail CD.

The simplest setup: copy @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe directly into
your existing LBA2 install folder — the one that contains lba2.hqr,
music\, video\, vox\, etc. — and run it from there. The engine
looks for game data in the directory the .exe is launched from.

If you'd rather keep @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe separate from your
game install, point it at the data with one of:

    @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe --game-dir "C:\path\to\game"

    set LBA2_GAME_DIR=C:\path\to\game
    @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe

The engine also auto-discovers a "data" or "game" subfolder next to
the .exe, so this layout works without flags too:

    @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe
    data\
        lba2.hqr
        music\
        video\
        ...


RUNNING
-------

Double-click @LBA2_EXECUTABLE_NAME@.exe, or run from cmd.exe /
PowerShell. If it can't find game data, the log file in your user
profile lists every directory it tried.


